# SPA fallback for Render's static hosting.
#
# Explicit entries for invite-link shapes first — some messaging apps garble
# the shared URL (e.g. pasting the whole message "Join my FutPools: Foo!
# https://…/p/CODE" into the address bar). The dedicated rules catch mangled
# shapes before the generic `/*` wildcard. Every rule rewrites (200) to the
# SPA index so React Router takes control and the client-side resolver pulls
# the clean 8-char code out of whatever path garbage arrived.
/p/*    /index.html   200
/c/*    /index.html   200
/*      /index.html   200
